U%20Photo%20Bank%2FNBCUniversal%20via%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Alfred%20Gescheidt%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMarcus%20Lemonis%20%E2%80%94%20the%20multimillionaire%20entrepreneur%20known%20for%20dishing%20out%20tough%20love%20tactics%20and%20advice%20to%20small%20businesses%20across%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20returned%20to%20reality%20television%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20episode%2C%20I'm%20meeting%20businesses%20at%20a%20crossroads%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20viewers%20during%20the%20double%20episode%20premiere%20of%20Fox's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fixer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20a%20consultant.%20I%20don't%20believe%20in%20handouts.%20I'm%20a%20capitalist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%202013%20to%202021%2C%20Lemonis%20also%20hosted%20another%20reality%20show%2C%20CNBC's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Profit.%26quot%3B%20Its%20premise%20was%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fixer%26quot%3B%3A%20Lemonis%20offered%20capital%20and%20advice%20to%20what%20were%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bstruggling%26quot%3B%20small%20businesses%20in%20exchange%20for%20partial%20ownership%20and%20being%20put%20%26quot%3B100%25%20in%20charge.%26quot%3B%20The%20show%20was%20a%20hit%20and%20turned%20Lemonis%20into%20a%20minor%20celebrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20resulted%20in%20a%20sprawling%20mess%20of%20lawsuits%2C%20arbitrations%2C%20confidential%20settlements%2C%20and%20small%20business%20owners%20who%20say%20that%20Lemonis%20damaged%20their%20companies%20and%20reputations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20roughly%20100%20businesses%20featured%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Profit%2C%26quot%3B%20more%20than%2050%20filed%20lawsuits%2C%20engaged%20in%20mediation%20talks%2C%20or%20settled%20with%20Lemonis%20and%20NBCUniversal%20over%20the%20harm%20they%20say%20they%20endured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20of%20these%20disputes%20were%20known%2C%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20fallout%20has%20not%20been%20previously%20reported.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20learned%20that%20in%202021%2C%20NBCUniversal%2C%20CNBC%2C%20Comcast%2C%20Lemonis%2C%20and%20the%20show's%20production%20company%20settled%20for%20%2411%20million%2C%20with%2040%20companies%20that%20appeared%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Profit%26quot%3B%20paid%20%24275%2C000%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArbitrators%20and%20federal%20judges%20dismissed%20several%20fraud%20and%20misconduct%20claims%20against%20Lemonis.%20In%20two%20cases%2C%20NBCUniversal%2C%20Lemonis%2C%20and%20their%20affiliated%20companies%20secured%20more%20than%20%2420%20million%20in%20judgments%2C%20loan%20repayments%2C%20and%20legal%20fee%20awards%20after%20lawsuits%20filed%20by%20companies%20that%20appeared%20on%20the%20show%20went%20to%20arbitration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marcus%20Lemonis%20during%20The%20Profit%20season%202.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688bbd3a3d5881a51c1e61c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELemonis%2C%2051%2C%20got%20his%20start%20selling%20cars%20and%20hustling%20RVs.%3Cp%3EHeidi%20Gutman%2FCNBC%2FNBCU%20Photo%20Bank%2FNBCUniversal%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20owners%20have%20accused%20Lemonis%20and%20NBCUniversal%20of%20aggressive%20tactics%2C%20broken%20promises%2C%20loading%20on%20debt%2C%20and%20deals%20that%20unraveled%20after%20filming.%20Business%20Insider%20interviewed%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20people%20involved%20with%20the%20show%20and%20reviewed%20thousands%20of%20pages%20of%20court%20records%2C%20correspondence%2C%20and%20confidential%20settlement%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELemonis%20and%20NBCUniversal%20have%20denied%20the%20allegations%2C%20saying%20the%20CEO%20was%20only%20trying%20to%20help%20companies%20already%20in%20trouble.%20In%20court%20and%20public%20statements%2C%20they've%20argued%20they%20disclosed%20key%20risks%20of%20appearing%20on%20the%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Lemonis%20said%20he%20had%20won%20%26quot%3Bany%20claim%20that%20was%20ever%20brought%20against%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20I%20didn't%20do%20anything%20wrong.%20I%20have%20a%20clean%20conscience.%20I%20sleep%20at%20night%20very%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Lemonis%20said.%20He%20declined%20to%20discuss%20the%20settlement%20agreement%20and%20didn't%20respond%20to%20subsequent%20follow-up%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20money%20that%20I%20could%20ever%20think%20of%20that%20got%20spent%20was%20mine%2C%26quot%3B%20Lemonis%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20that%20I%20ever%20got%20out%20of%20the%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20including%20loans%2C%20interest%2C%20in%20any%20business%20of%20any%20kind%20%E2%80%94%20this%20isn't%20specific%20to%20any%20business%20%E2%80%94%20was%20zero.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Fox%20has%20brought%20Lemonis%20back%20to%20the%20air%20with%20a%20familiar%20concept.%20Fox%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc423c20-ec9c-4307-b26f-adf824ba595e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'100%25%20in%20charge'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELemonis%2C%2051%2C%20got%20his%20start%20selling%20cars%20and%20hustling%20RVs%2C%20snapping%20up%20dealerships%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20that%20he%20rolled%20into%20a%20national%20chain.%20He%20became%20the%20CEO%20of%20Camping%20World%20in%202006%20and%20took%20the%20RV%20giant%20public%20a%20decade%20later.%20As%20his%20profile%20grew%2C%20he%20styled%20himself%20as%20a%20sharp-tongued%2C%20blue-collar%20mogul%20%E2%80%94%20part%20businessman%2C%20part%20showman.%20In%202024%2C%20he%20took%20over%20as%20executive%20chairman%20of%20Beyond%2C%20Inc.%2C%20the%20parent%20company%20of%20Bed%20Bath%20%26amp%3B%20Beyond%2C%20shortly%20after%20the%20home%20goods%20brand%20declared%20bankruptcy.%20He%20was%20appointed%20principal%20executive%20officer%20a%20year%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Profit%26quot%3B%20first%20aired%20in%20July%202013%2C%20part%20of%20an%20attempt%20by%20CNBC%20%E2%80%94%20NBCUniversal's%20business%20news%20channel%20%E2%80%94%20to%20find%20programming%20for%20the%20after-market%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20was%20simple.%20Lemonis%20promised%20to%20invest%20his%20money%2C%20often%20in%20exchange%20for%20an%20ownership%20stake%2C%20to%20help%20revamp%20small%20businesses%20across%20the%20country.%20He%20would%20negotiate%20on-air%2C%20handshake%20agreements%20with%20business%20owners%20and%20declare%20himself%20%26quot%3B100%25%20in%20charge%26quot%3B%20before%20implementing%20a%20slew%20of%20changes.%20If%20owners%20expressed%20doubt%2C%20Lemonis%20and%20producers%20told%20them%20to%20%26quot%3Btrust%20the%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20business%20owners%20alleged%20in%20legal%20and%20mediation%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marcus%20Lemonis%20during%20season%201%20of%20The%20Profit.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688bbcbc85e81483682f0fdb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222832%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Profit%26quot%3B%20ran%20from%202013%20to%202021.%3Cp%3EVirginia%20Sherwood%2FCNBC%2FNBCU%20Photo%20Bank%2FNBCUniversal%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20show%20took%20off%20on%20social%20media%20and%2C%20within%20three%20years%2C%20CNBC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2015%2F10%2F30%2Fthe-profit-sets-cnbc-primetime-record.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20it%20was%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20most-watched%20original%20series%20telecast%20with%201.9%20million%20viewers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%202021%2C%20Gerard%20Fox%2C%20a%20Los%20Angeles-based%20litigator%20with%20a%20background%20in%20high-profile%20commercial%20and%20entertainment%20law%2C%20sent%20a%20series%20of%20letters%20to%20lawyers%20at%20Comcast%2C%20the%20parent%20company%20of%20NBCUniversal.%20The%20letters%2C%20which%20have%20been%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%20and%20have%20never%20previously%20been%20reported%20on%2C%20were%20put%20together%20on%20behalf%20of%20dozens%20of%20participants%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Profit%2C%26quot%3B%20detailing%20what%20they%20described%20as%20their%20negative%20experiences%20with%20the%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Fox%20sent%20his%20letters%2C%20both%20sides%20entered%20into%20mediation%2C%20according%20to%20one%20person%20involved%2C%20heading%20off%20potential%20litigation%20by%20many%20of%20the%20businesses.%20The%20settlement%20agreement%20was%20signed%20by%20senior%20executives%20at%20Comcast%2C%20NBCUniversal%2C%20CNBC%2C%20Lemonis%2C%20and%20the%20production%20company%2C%20and%20included%20non-disparagement%20clauses%20for%20the%20companies%20involved%20and%20a%20reciprocal%20confidentiality%20clause.%20Parties%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20settlement%20denied%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20small%20business%20owners%20said%20they%20took%20the%20money%20because%20they%20feared%20that%20otherwise%2C%20%26quot%3BNBC%20and%20Lemonis%20will%20throw%20%24millions%20at%20us%20and%20in%20the%20end%20squash%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20emails%20among%20business%20owners%20discussing%20the%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGerard%20Fox%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%20After%20a%20lawsuit%20he%20filed%20on%20behalf%20of%20another%20business%20that%20appeared%20on%20the%20show%20was%20dismissed%20in%20federal%20court%2C%20a%20judge%20sanctioned%20Fox%2C%20saying%20she%20was%20misled%20about%20the%20terms%20of%20that%20dismissal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20of%20'The%20Profit'%20was%20to%20help%20participants%20find%20a%20path%20to%20success%20for%20businesses%20that%20were%20often%20close%20to%20failure%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20CNBC%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20some%20did%20not%20succeed%2C%20the%20show%20aimed%20to%20help%20businesses%20get%20to%20profitability%20and%20shine%20a%20light%20on%20the%20challenges%20that%20face%20small%20business%20owners%20across%20the%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Still%20from%20the%20Detroit%20Denim%20episode%20of%20The%20Profit.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688bbdae85e81483682f0ff9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222143%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELemonis%20appeared%20with%20a%20denim%20business%20in%20one%20of%20the%20show's%20episode.%3Cp%3EScott%20Legato%2FCNBC%2FNBCU%20Photo%20Bank%2FNBCUniversal%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20document%20prepared%20for%20the%20mediation%2C%20the%20network%20said%20it%20had%20no%20role%20in%20the%20deals%20between%20Lemonis%20and%20the%20businesses%2C%20and%20that%20it%20wasn't%20responsible%20for%20how%20those%20deals%20turned%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20business%20owners%20declined%20to%20comment%2C%20with%20some%20citing%20contracts%20they%20signed%20prior%20to%20filming%20that%20stipulated%20heavy%20fines%20for%20speaking%20about%20the%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20NBCUniversal%20and%20the%20production%20company%20settled%20with%20five%20more%20businesses%2C%20which%20were%20represented%20by%20the%20law%20firm%20Quinn%20Emanuel%2C%20according%20to%20court%20documents.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20NBCUniversal%20also%20settled%20with%20the%20owners%20of%20an%20Illinois%20marina%20company%20who%20claimed%20that%20their%20business%20was%20disparaged%20on%20the%20show.%20Lemonis%20was%20not%20a%20party%20to%20these%20settlements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephen%20Marmer%2C%20a%20psychiatrist%20who%20has%20taught%20at%20UCLA's%20School%20of%20Medicine%2C%20was%20hired%20by%20the%20attorney%20Fox%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20companies%20for%20the%20settlement%20discussions.%20Marmer%20wrote%20in%20a%20report%20how%2C%20after%20interviewing%2048%20of%20the%20business%20owners%20or%20their%20family%20members%2C%20many%20described%20damage%20to%20their%20confidence%20or%20self-trust%2C%20humiliation%20in%20front%20of%20vendors%20or%20staff%2C%20or%20alienation%20from%20family%20members%20and%20business%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20five%20people%20said%20they%20had%20been%20suicidal%20or%20engaged%20in%20suicidal%20ideation%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20narratives%20presented%20in%20these%20interviews%20reflect%20what%20actually%20happened%20to%20those%20whom%20I%20interviewed%2C%20I%20can%20see%20how%20they%20were%20injured%20and%20how%20and%20why%20their%20symptoms%20arose%2C%26quot%3B%20Marmer%20concluded.%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20them%20will%20need%20ongoing%20treatment%20to%20recover%20from%20the%20PTSD%20and%20gaslighting%20they%20experienced.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20surprised%20that%20CNBC%20stuck%20with%20him%20as%20long%20as%20they%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dan%20Isenhart%2C%20a%20longtime%20employee%20at%20the%20Southern%20California%20wine%20shop%20Amazing%20Grapes%2C%20which%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%20three%20years%20after%20appearing%20on%20the%20show%20and%20was%20not%20part%20of%20the%20settlement.%20%26quot%3BHe%20caused%20a%20lot%20of%20heartache%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216118bcc-c147-4549-8855-42f2d376814c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBankruptcy%2C%20litigation%2C%20and%20debt%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20companies%2C%20appearing%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Profit%26quot%3B%20was%20a%20boon.%20Mike%20Anderson%20said%20revenue%20for%20his%20and%20his%20brother's%20business%2C%20now%20focused%20on%20screen%20printing%2C%20is%2010%20times%20what%20it%20was%20when%20they%20filmed%20their%20show.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20night-and-day%20difference%2C%26quot%3B%20Anderson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20business%20owner%2C%20Ana%20Quincoces%2C%20said%20her%20ongoing%20relationship%20with%20Lemonis%20has%20been%20fruitful%2C%20including%20work%20he%20directed%20her%20way.%20The%20two%20considered%20opening%20a%20restaurant%20together%2C%20she%20said.%20Quincoces%20added%20that%20her%20prior%20experience%20with%20reality%20TV%20%E2%80%94%20she%20appeared%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Real%20Housewives%20of%20Miami%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20may%20have%20better%20prepared%20her%20for%20the%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20feel%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202021%2C%20Steve%20Weissmann's%20business%2C%20Tumbleweed%20Tiny%20House%2C%20was%20bankrupt%2C%20embroiled%20in%20litigation%20it%20would%20ultimately%20lose%2C%20and%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20debt%20to%20Lemonis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steve%20Weissmann%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Tumbleweed%20Tiny%20House%20Company%20and%20Marcus%20Lemonis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688bbe3085e81483682f100c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222002%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELemonis%20and%20Steve%20Weissmann.%3Cp%3EThomas%20Cooper%2FCNBC%2FNBCU%20Photo%20Bank%2FNBCUniversal%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20when%20Weissmann%20appeared%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Profit%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20described%20his%20business%20in%20court%20documents%20as%20successful%2C%20making%20millions%20in%20revenue%2C%20and%20meeting%20with%20potential%20investors.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20growing%20at%2060%20percent%20compound%20annual%20growth%20rates%2C%20which%20is%20very%20successful%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20were%20losing%20money%20as%20we%20grew%20too%20fast.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20he%20initially%20applied%20to%20be%20on%20the%20show%20because%20he%20was%20impressed%20by%20Lemonis's%20reputation%20as%20a%20business%20guru.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20first%20day%20of%20filming%2C%20Lemonis%20expressed%20concern%20at%20the%20way%20Weissmann%20accounted%20for%20customer%20deposits%2C%20Weissmann%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Weissmann%20asked%20Lemonis%20what%20the%20future%20of%20the%20company%20looked%20like%20to%20him%2C%20Lemonis%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20not%20going%20to%20jail%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20transcript%20from%20the%20taping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20went%20home%20after%20filming%2C%20Weissmann%20said%20he%20held%20his%20wife%20while%20they%20cried%2C%20and%20she%20vomited.%20Weissmann%2C%20who%20said%20that%20his%20accounting%20was%20above%20board%2C%20said%20he%20decided%20to%20take%20the%20deal%20offered%20on-air%20or%20risk%20being%20called%20a%20criminal%20on%20TV.%20The%20footage%20never%20aired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20did%20make%20it%20to%20air%20was%20Weissmann%20telling%20Lemonis%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20running%20on%20the%20edge.%26quot%3B%20They%20ultimately%20verbally%20agreed%20to%20a%20deal%20that%20involved%20Lemonis%20loaning%20%243%20million%20to%20the%20business%20in%20exchange%20for%2075%25%20ownership.%20It%20also%20involved%20a%20radical%20change%20to%20Tumbleweed's%20business%20model.%20Lemonis%20told%20Weissmann%20to%20move%20Tumbleweed%20away%20from%20custom%20builds%20and%20toward%20standard%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeissmann%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20questioned%20the%20move%20%E2%80%94%20most%20customers%20preferred%20custom%20models%2C%20he%20said%20%E2%80%94%20but%20agreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20statements%20in%20court%20filings%2C%20after%20the%20episode%20aired%2C%20Lemonis%20eventually%20stopped%20responding%2C%20and%20Tumbleweed%20was%20left%20with%20excess%20inventory%20from%20the%20production%20of%20standard%20units.%20After%20months%20of%20turning%20down%20orders%20for%20custom%20homes%2C%20Tumbleweed%20started%20to%20run%20out%20of%20cash%2C%20according%20to%20statements%20in%20court%20documents.%20Along%20the%20way%2C%20Tumbleweed%20also%20took%20on%20loans%20of%20around%20%242.8%20million%20from%20a%20Lemonis%20company%20to%20stay%20afloat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steve%20Weissmann%20and%20Marcus%20Lemonis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688bbe803d5881a51c1e61f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222002%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWeissmann's%20company%20declared%20bankruptcy%20in%202020.%3Cp%3EThomas%20Cooper%2FCNBC%2FNBCU%20Photo%20Bank%2FNBCUniversal%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20three%20years%20after%20appearing%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Profit%2C%26quot%3B%20in%202020%2C%20Tumbleweed%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%2C%20which%20Weissmann%20called%20%26quot%3Bdevastating.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20he%20wasn't%20involved%20in%20the%20%2411%20million%20settlement%20because%20he%20was%20already%20involved%20in%20these%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Lemonis%20company%20sued%20Weissmann%20a%20year%20later%2C%20seeking%20the%20nearly%20%243%20million%20in%20principal%20and%20interest%20on%20loans%20made%20to%20Tumbleweed%2C%20for%20which%20Weissmann%20was%20a%20guarantor.%20Lemonis'%20lawyers%20argued%20that%20the%20bankruptcy%20filing%20had%20triggered%20an%20immediate%20obligation%20to%20pay%20back%20the%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeissmann%20responded%20by%20filing%20a%20counterclaim%20and%20then%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20NBCUniversal%2C%20Lemonis%2C%20the%20production%20company%2C%20alleging%20fraud%20and%20breaches%20of%20fiduciary%20duty%2C%20among%20other%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20went%20to%20arbitration%2C%20as%20required%20by%20the%20show's%20participation%20contract.%20An%20arbitrator%20sided%20with%20the%20defendants%2C%20writing%20%26quot%3Bthe%20weight%20of%20the%20evidence%20shows%20that%20Lemonis%20was%20attempting%20to%20'save'%20Tumbleweed%2C%20not%20have%20it%20fail%2C%20even%20if%20he%20did%20not%20ultimately%20succeed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20July%2C%20a%20judge%20confirmed%20a%20%2414.4%20million%20arbitration%20award%20to%20NBCUniversal%2C%20Lemonis%2C%20Camping%20World%2C%20and%20the%20production%20company%20against%20Weissmann%20and%20Tumbleweed%2C%20including%20%247.7%20million%20in%20attorney%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELemonis%20and%20NBCUniversal%20secured%20another%20win%20in%202023.%20An%20arbitrator%20awarded%20%247.1%20million%2C%20including%20more%20than%20%246%20million%20in%20attorney%20fees%2C%20to%20NBCUniversal%2C%20the%20production%20company%2C%20and%20Camping%20World%20after%20the%20trustee%20of%20the%20bankrupt%20design%20firm%20Precise%20Graphix%20lost%20in%20arbitration.%20The%20arbitrator%20cited%20%26quot%3Bthe%20complete%20failure%20of%20competent%2C%20credible%20evidence%26quot%3B%20to%20support%20the%20trustee's%20allegations%2C%20which%20included%20fraud%20and%20breach%20of%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marcus%20Lemonis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688bc0f9f748d8c055f6a9cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222002%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELemonis's%20new%20show%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fixer%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20a%20premise%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Profit.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EThomas%20Cooper%2FCNBC%2FNBCU%20Photo%20Bank%2FNBCUniversal%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f04dc1e2-d864-4f12-a1cd-68dffb77f394%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20'prop'%20check%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20business%20owners%20allege%20that%20Lemonis%20took%20advantage%20of%20companies%20he%20pledged%20to%20help%2C%20according%20to%20interviews%20and%20legal%20records%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20Many%20of%20the%20allegations%20of%20exploitative%20business%20practices%20were%20also%20detailed%20in%20a%202018%20Inc.%20Magazine%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%202016%20lawsuit%2C%20the%20owners%20of%20a%20Pennsylvania-based%20restaurant%20franchise%2C%20My%20Big%20Fat%20Greek%20Gyro%2C%20said%20they%20applied%20in%20hopes%20of%20expanding%20and%20selling%20more%20franchises.%20While%20filming%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20said%2C%20they%20agreed%20to%20a%20deal%20with%20Lemonis%20for%20%24350%2C000%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%2055%25%20stake%20in%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20cameras%20were%20off%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20alleged%2C%20the%20owners%20were%20told%20to%20return%20the%20check%20they%20received%20from%20Lemonis%2C%20and%20that%20it%20was%20just%20a%20%26quot%3Bprop%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20show.%20The%20owners%20claimed%20that%20they%20never%20received%20the%20money%2C%20and%20that%20Lemonis%20used%20the%20promised%20funds%20for%20renovations%2C%20changed%20the%20businesses'%20name%20to%20The%20Simple%20Greek%2C%20while%20ultimately%20%26quot%3Bfreezing%26quot%3B%20them%20out%20of%20their%20business%20after%20establishing%20a%20new%20LLC%20that%20was%20owned%20by%20a%20Lemonis%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrior%20to%20the%20show%2C%20we%20were%20collectively%20making%20about%20%24160%2C000%20a%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20owner%20said%20in%20a%202022%20deposition.%20%26quot%3BEighteen%20months%20into%20the%20show%2C%20we%20had%20no%20income.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20which%20alleged%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20fraud%2C%20breach%20of%20contract%2C%20and%20breach%20of%20fiduciary%20duty%2C%20is%20ongoing%20in%20state%20court.%20Lawyers%20for%20Lemonis%20have%20called%20the%20claims%20%26quot%3Bbaseless%2C%26quot%3B%20arguing%20he%20invested%20millions%20of%20dollars%20to%20try%20to%20%26quot%3Bsalvage%20plaintiffs'%20floundering%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20allegations%20of%20misconduct%20were%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20Lemonis%20%26quot%3Boperating%20the%20business%20pursuant%20to%20his%20undisputed%20decision-making%20powers%20as%20the%20controlling%20owner%20of%20The%20Simple%20Greek.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202020%20lawsuit%20filed%20by%20the%20New%20York%20company%20Bowery%20Kitchen%20Supplies%2C%20the%20owner%20alleged%20that%20after%20agreeing%20to%20an%20on-air%20deal%20for%20%24350%2C000%20in%20exchange%20for%2033%25%20of%20the%20business%2C%20a%20producer%20took%20back%20the%20%26quot%3Bprop%26quot%3B%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20Greek%20restaurant%20owners%2C%20he%20alleged%20that%20he%20never%20received%20the%20promised%20funding%2C%20and%20that%20Lemonis%20made%20drastic%20changes%20to%20the%20business%2C%20including%20liquidating%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars'%20worth%20of%20inventory%20and%20shutting%20down%20the%20store%20for%20costly%20renovations%2C%20leaving%20the%20business%20deep%20in%20debt.%20The%20case%20was%20later%20dismissed%20as%20part%20of%20the%202021%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2010%20companies%20or%20business%20owners%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%20after%20appearing%20on%20the%20show%2C%20court%20records%20show.%20Another%2017%20closed%20down%2C%20according%20to%20the%20letters%20that%20Fox%2C%20the%20attorney%2C%20sent%20to%20Comcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22407017f7-1cd4-4eda-aa3c-3dd753881699%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'We%20have%20been%20diminished'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202021%20settlement%20talks%20were%20not%20the%20first%20time%20that%20participants%20on%20the%20show%20attempted%20to%20notify%20NBCUniversal%20about%20their%20complaints%2C%20according%20to%20Fox's%20letters%20and%20other%20records%20obtained%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20a%20business%20owner%20hired%20an%20attorney%20to%20prevent%20NBCUniversal%20from%20airing%20their%20episode%2C%20after%20they%20said%20misrepresentations%20were%20made%20during%20filming%2C%20the%20letters%20say.%20The%20network%20declined%2C%20and%20the%20episode%20came%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20daughter%20of%20a%20business%20owner%20who%20appeared%20on%20the%20show%20also%20said%20online%20that%20her%20family%20was%20humiliated%20by%20Lemonis%20and%20the%20production%20company.%20The%20executive%20producer%20told%20her%20in%20late%202014%20that%20%26quot%3BCNBC%20lawyers%20had%20seen%20the%20post%20and%20were%20not%20happy%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20she'd%20be%20sued%20by%20the%20network%20if%20she%20didn't%20take%20it%20down%2C%20the%20letters%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marcus%20Lemonis%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Profit%26quot%3B%20speaks%20during%20AOL%20Build%20at%20AOL%20Studios%20In%20New%20York%20on%20December%203%2C%202015%20in%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688bc0043d5881a51c1e6234%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221837%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELemonis%20during%20a%202015%20event%20with%20AOL.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Lamparski%2FWireImage%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20year%2C%20the%20family%20member%20of%20a%20different%20business%20owner%20wrote%20to%20CNBC's%20president%20and%20chairman%3B%20NBCUniversal's%20CEO%3B%20and%20several%20other%20network%20executives.%20She%20said%20the%20show%20portrayed%20her%20family%20in%20a%20false%20light%20and%20defamed%20them%2C%20according%20to%20the%20letters.%20In%202015%2C%20another%20owner%20sent%20%26quot%3Ba%20detailed%20letter%26quot%3B%20to%20NBCUniversal%2C%20%26quot%3Binforming%20them%20of%20the%20fraud%20and%20defamation%20that%20the%20show%20and%20Lemonis%20perpetrated%20on%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20letters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20speaking%20on%20the%20%26quot%3BShark%20Tank%20Podcast%26quot%3B%20in%202015%2C%20Lemonis%20said%20that%20following%20one%20of%20the%20episodes%2C%20he%20%26quot%3Bgot%20emails%20from%20the%20family%20and%20aunts%20and%20uncles%20and%20cousins%20and%20how%20upset%20they%20were%20that%20I%20had%20portrayed%20them%20that%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECNBC%20aired%20the%20show's%20final%20episode%20in%20September%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20as%20another%20batch%20of%20businesses%20appear%20on%20Fox's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fixer%2C%26quot%3B%20Steve%20Weissmann%20says%20he%20wishes%20he'd%20never%20said%20yes%20to%20%26quot%3BThe%20Profit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20been%20diminished%20in%20a%20way%20that%20we%20never%20deserved%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Weissmann%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20on%20a%20reality%20television%20show%20and%20made%20to%20look%20like%20an%20idiot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%20about%20reality%20TV%2C%20Hollywood%2C%20or%20the%20networks%3F%20Contact%20Nicole%20Einbinder%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aneinbinder%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eneinbinder%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20neinbinder.70.%20Contact%20Dakin%20Campbell%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Adcampbell%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Edcampbell%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20dakin.11.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-profit-marcus-lemonis-lawsuits-settlements-the-fixer-fox-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754039401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688bbc04f748d8c055f6a91e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider