nia%2C%20Texas%2C%20Kansas%2C%20and%20California%2C%20are%20considering%20or%20have%20proposed%20implementing%20special%20tariffs%20for%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tariffs%20are%20a%20response%20to%20the%20unprecedented%20demand%20for%20electricity%20coming%20from%20Big%20Tech's%20AI%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestor-owned%20utilities%20in%20the%20US%20are%20on%20track%20to%20build%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eei.org%2FNews%2Fnews%2FAll%2Feei-releases-2024-financial-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241.1%20trillion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20new%20infrastructure%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%20largely%20to%20keep%20pace%20with%20that%20demand%2C%20according%20to%20industry%20group%20Edison%20Electric%20Institute.%20About%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eia.gov%2Ftodayinenergy%2Fdetail.php%3Fid%3D40913%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E72%25%20of%20electricity%20customers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20are%20served%20by%20investor-owned%20utilities%2C%20which%20profit%20by%20building%20new%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20business%20model%20was%20born%20when%20population%20growth%20and%20economic%20development%20drove%20electricity%20demand%2C%20and%20everyone%20was%20thought%20to%20benefit%20from%20system-wide%20upgrades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-center-cost-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edriving%3C%2Fa%3E%20most%20of%20today's%20electricity%20demand%2C%20some%20are%20questioning%20which%20customers%20exactly%20should%20pay%20for%20upgrades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20really%20need%20to%20think%20about%20who%20should%20pay%20for%20this%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20Ari%20Peskoe%2C%20Director%20of%20Harvard%20Law%20School's%20Electricity%20Law%20Initiative%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20it's%20fair%20to%20just%20have%20these%20very%20wealthy%20corporations%20come%20in%20and%20force%20utilities%20to%20build%20more%20infrastructure%20and%20then%20just%20socialize%20the%20costs%20the%20way%20we%20normally%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b7508c39-644f-4788-b831-903618816ad6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20am%20I%20subsidizing%20Big%20Tech's%20power%20bill%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20state%20regulators%20have%20allowed%20public%20utilities%20to%20recover%20the%20cost%20of%20investment%2C%20plus%20a%20rate%20of%20return%2C%20of%20new%20transmission%20lines%20and%20power%20plants%20by%20raising%20rates%20for%20all%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20utility%20business%20model%20was%20based%20on%20the%20assumption%20that%20society%20benefited%20from%20the%20grid's%20expansion%3B%20therefore%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20should%20all%20pay%20for%20the%20infrastructure%20needed%20to%20allow%20for%20its%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Peskoe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStaggering%20data%20center%20power%20demand%20has%20flipped%20this%20assumption%20on%20its%20head.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20residential%20electricity%20use%20is%20going%20down%2C%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20stand%20to%20gain%20the%20most%20from%20major%20utility%20expansion.%20Under%20the%20old%20rules%20of%20cost%20allocation%2C%20everyone%20else%20might%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Louisiana%2C%20customers%20of%20the%20state's%20major%20public%20utility%20could%20be%20responsible%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-data-center-louisiana-5b-ratepayers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%245%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20costs%20associated%20with%20new%20natural%20gas%20plants%20and%20transmission%20lines%20needed%20to%20serve%20a%20Meta%20data%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWisconsin%20ratepayers%20could%20pay%20for%20a%20%242%20million%20transmission%20project%20for%20Microsoft's%20data%20center%20campus%20outside%20Milwaukee.%20In%20Colorado%2C%20Xcel%20Energy%20customers%20could%20end%20up%20paying%20%241.7%20billion%20for%20new%20transmission%20lines%20to%20serve%20the%20state's%20growing%20data%20center%20load.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222bdfca1d-5900-482c-a8b4-e8ec64335412%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20states%20doing%20about%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20Indiana%20regulators%20approved%20changes%20to%20Indiana%20Michigan%20Power%20Company's%20tariff%20for%20large%20industrial%20customers%2C%20setting%20the%20terms%20for%20connecting%20data%20center%20customers%20to%20the%20grid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%20were%20part%20of%20a%20settlement%20agreement%20between%20I%26amp%3BM%2C%20its%20three%20largest%20data%20center%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20Amazon%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20Google%20%E2%80%94%20consumer%20advocacy%20groups%2C%20and%20the%20Data%20Center%20Coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20revised%20tariff%20requires%20%26quot%3Blarge%20load%26quot%3B%20customers%20that%20use%20a%20lot%20of%20electricity%20to%20make%20%26quot%3Blong-term%20financial%20commitments%20proportional%20to%20their%20size%2C%26quot%3B%20I%26amp%3BM%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aep.com%2Fnews%2Fstories%2Fview%2F10037%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20centers%20are%20driving%20record%20load%20growth%20in%20the%20utility's%20Indiana%20service%20territory.%20Peak%20load%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highest%20amount%20of%20electricity%20used%20by%20customers%20at%20a%20time%20%E2%80%94%20is%20on%20track%20to%20more%20than%20double%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20Inskeep%2C%20program%20director%20at%20Citizens%20Action%20Coalition%20Indiana%2C%20a%20participant%20in%20the%20IMP%20settlement%2C%20said%20the%20revised%20tariff%20will%20help%20protect%20ratepayers%20from%20the%20cost%20of%20%26quot%3Bstranded%20assets%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20infrastructure%20that%20gets%20built%2C%20but%20ultimately%20doesn't%20get%20used.%20But%20it%20doesn't%20address%20several%20other%20aspects%20of%20data%20center%20growth%20that%20could%20show%20up%20in%20consumer%20electricity%20bills%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20factors%20account%20for%20the%20final%20number%20that%20customers%20see%20on%20a%20monthly%20electric%20bill%2C%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20new%20infrastructure%20is%20just%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20really%20high%20load%20growth%20from%20data%20centers%20driving%20the%20cost%20of%20capacity%20super%20high%20and%20driving%20the%20cost%20of%20building%20new%20resources%20super%20high%2C%20and%20those%20costs%20could%20still%20end%20up%20in%20consumer%20bills%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Inskeep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20its%20part%2C%20Big%20Tech%20is%20fighting%20to%20keep%20its%20own%20electric%20bills%20from%20rising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Ohio%2C%20a%20lawyer%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdis.puc.state.oh.us%2FViewImage.aspx%3FCMID%3DA1001001A25D09B64704F00675%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20regulators%20that%20AEP%20had%20%26quot%3Bsingled%20out%26quot%3B%20data%20centers%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bdiscriminatory%20tariff.%26quot%3B%20A%20lawyer%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdis.puc.state.oh.us%2FDocumentRecord.aspx%3FDocID%3Dd152733f-b899-4ab2-8d9c-a7b65514e6f3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20the%20tariff%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeparture%20from%20the%20fundamental%20rules%26quot%3B%20of%20utility%20regulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20exactly%20the%20point%2C%20said%20Peskoe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20really%20need%20is%20a%20new%20approach%20to%20allocating%20the%20utilities'%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Peskoe.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20a%20lot%20of%20this%20comes%20down%20to%20%E2%80%94%20making%20sure%20that%20the%20data%20centers%20are%20paying%20for%20infrastructure%20that's%20serving%20them%2C%20that's%20being%20built%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20