edge%3A%20'I'm%20so%20close%20to%20the%20finish%20line'%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20previously%20criticized%20the%20interest%20charge%20restart%20and%20urged%20the%20administration%20to%20reverse%20course.%20On%20July%2014%2C%20Sens.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%2C%20Bernie%20Sanders%2C%20and%20Chuck%20Schumer%20sent%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.warren.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Fletter_to_ed_re_interest_charges_in_save_forbearance.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20McMahon%20saying%20that%20the%20restart%20is%20%26quot%3Bdevastating%20for%20millions%20of%20American%20families.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20defies%20logic%20and%20the%20law%20that%20a%20months-old%20preliminary%20injunction%20against%20SAVE%2C%20which%20makes%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20interest-free%20forbearance%2C%20requires%20you%20to%20start%20charging%20interest%20to%20millions%20of%20borrowers%20in%20forbearance%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawmakers%20also%20cited%20a%20backlog%20in%20income-driven%20repayment%20plan%20processing%20that%20would%20make%20it%20difficult%20for%20borrowers%20on%20SAVE%20to%20switch%20to%20a%20new%20plan.%20While%20the%20department%20said%20in%20its%20press%20release%20announcing%20the%20interest%20charges%20that%20borrowers%20who%20switch%20to%20a%20new%20plan%20%26quot%3Bcan%20expect%20quick%20and%20timely%20processing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20department%20in%20May%20reported%20a%20backlog%20of%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-waiting-idr-affordable-repayment-plans-education-department-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E2%20million%20income-driven%20repayment%20applications%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20income-based%20repayment%20plan%2C%20which%20the%20department%20specifically%20mentioned%20as%20a%20viable%20option%20for%20SAVE%20borrowers%2C%20is%20also