doom.%20However%20in%20pursuit%20of%20solutions%20to%20bolster%20our%20future%2C%20one%20must%20look%20back%20into%20the%20past%20where%20earlier%20civilizations%20have%20battled%20similar%2C%20if%20not%20the%20same%2C%20challenges%20around%20water%20scarcity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20floods%20to%20droughts%2C%20one%20can%20find%20an%20array%20of%20eco-friendly%20and%20sustainable%20traditional%20methods%20of%20water%20conservation%20in%20the%20pages%20of%20history%2C%20that%20have%20not%20only%20saved%20millions%20of%20lives%20but%20have%20also%20stood%20the%20test%20of%20time.%20Almost%20every%20region%20in%20India%20is%20blessed%20with%20these%20homegrown%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F384890%2Fmerino-industries-water-conservation-water-management-ponds-reservoirs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewater%20harvesting%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20conservation%20techniques%20that%20are%20tailored%20to%20fit%20the%20unique%20geographical%20and%20cultural%20needs%20of%20the%20place%20and%20the%20community%20inhabiting%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20World%20Water%20Day%20we%20pledged%20to%20delve%20into%20the%20pages%20of%20history%20and%20highlight%20some%20of%20the%20significant%20sustainable%20water%20conservation%20methods%20practised%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EAhar%20Pynes%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-280153%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ahars%20are%20used%20for%20irrigation%20during%20dry%20months%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-1648033853-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-280153%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAhars%20are%20used%20for%20irrigation%20during%20dry%20months.%20Picture%20Credits%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiawaterportal.org%2Farticles%2Fahar-pynes-traditional-flood-water-harvesting-systems-can-help-revive-agriculture-south%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndia%20Water%20Portal%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrevalent%20in%20South%20Bihar%2C%20Ahar%20Pynes%20are%20traditional%20floodwater%20harvesting%20systems%20that%20work%20as%20reservoirs%20to%20cut%20the%20flow%20of%20water%20and%20store%20it%20for%20irrigation%20and%20other%20purposes.%20These%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F447032%2Fshyam-sunder-jyani-teacher-turned-environmentalist-restored-mining-wasteland-in-rajasthan-with-community-support%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20reservoirs%20%3C%2Fa%3Eare%20made%20with%20embankments%20on%20three%20sides%20that%20are%20situated%20at%20the%20end%20of%20diversion%20channels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20diversion%20channels%20known%20as%20pynes%20are%20artificial%20rivulets%20that%20are%20extended%20from%20rivers%20to%20collect%20water%20and%20channel%20it%20to%20the%20Ahars%20for%20irrigation%20during%20dry%20months.%20In%20a%20state%20that%20is%20largely%20known%20for%20its%20agricultural%20contribution%2C%20especially%20paddy%20cultivation%2C%20this%20technique%20of%20using%20Ahar%20Pynes%20is%20excep